I respect his abilities but I think his record is padded due to the fact that there hasn't been much comp during his career and he ducked one of the better fighters of this generation in Pacquiao until he was past his prime. I think he still would've beaten Pacquiao in his prime just because of his incredible speed and defensive style. As a general human being and role model I've got nothing for him. Like him or not (I don't), he is a true master of his craft for his style of boxing, he's just not very exciting to watch. Lennox Lewis had the same problem in his day. For me, I prefer MMA anymore.
